    "headline": "Ericsson slightly lags profit expectations as AI demand drives up chip costs",
    "summary": "Sweden's Ericsson reported a first-quarter core profit that slightly missed market ‌expectations on Friday, citing increasing chip ‌costs caused by artificial intelligence demand and a sales slowdown ​in North America. The company reported an adjusted operating profit of 5.2 billion Swedish crowns ($566 million), excluding restructuring charges, for the first quarter of ‌2026. Analysts polled ⁠by Infront were expecting 5.4 billion crowns on average.",
